        <definition>void XIic_MultiMasterInclude</definition>
        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>XIic_MultiMasterInclude</name>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function includes multi-master code such that multi-master events are handled properly. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Multi-master events include a loss of arbitration and the bus transitioning from busy to not busy. This function allows the multi-master processing to be optional. This function must be called prior to allowing any multi-master events to occur, such as after the driver is initialized.</para><para><simplesect kind="return"><para>None.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
